  "texts": [
    "These low-rank matrices, typically with ranks of 4, 8, or 16, are optimized during fine-tuning, allowing adaptation to downstream tasks without modifying the billions of parameters in the original backbone model.",
    "This greatly reduces the number of trainable parameters and computational costs, making it feasible to fine-tune large models on commodity GPUs without sacrificing much performance.QLoRA.",
    "Quantized LoRA (QLoRA) [2] builds upon LoRA by introducing 4-bit and 8-bit quantization to store model weights more efficiently.",
    "This combination allows fine-tuning of large-scale models on GPUs with limited memory capacity.",
    "QLoRA uses techniques such as double quantization and NF4 (Nor-malFloat4) precision to minimize the loss in performance introduced by quantization while ensuring that memory consumption remains manageable."
  ],
